        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer18081563" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12038812852251626121">This book is a family saga on the Godwin&apos;s family told over a period of fifty years in their Welsh estate, Oxmoon. I must agree with Misfit, this book is without any doubt the best book written by Susan Howatch, even if I did loved Cashelmara and Penmarric. The parallel with the real historical characters is fabulous. As in any book by SH, is hard to tell which is my favorite character but I&apos;m still divided between Kester and Hal.</span>
  <span id="freeText12038812852251626121" style="display:none">This book is a family saga on the Godwin's family told over a period of fifty years in their Welsh estate, Oxmoon. I must agree with Misfit, this book is without any doubt the best book written by Susan Howatch, even if I did loved Cashelmara and Penmarric. The parallel with the real historical characters is fabulous. As in any book by SH, is hard to tell which is my favorite character but I'm still divided between Kester and Hal.</span>
